I"¶<h1 id="diagram">Diagram</h1>

<p>Ports can be connected to one another.</p>

<p>[<em>Only ports can be connected.</em>]</p>

<p><img src="https://github.com/guitarvydas/guitarvydas.github.io/blob/master/assets/2021-07-30%20Connections.png?raw=true" alt="2021-07-30 Connections.png" /></p>

<p>Connections are shown as arrows.</p>

<p>Connections appear in the factbase as 3 facts:</p>

<ol>
  <li>A declaration, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">edge(e,'').</code></li>
  <li>A source port, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">source(e,a).</code></li>
  <li>A target port, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">target(e,c).</code></li>
</ol>

<h1 id="processing-connections">Processing Connections</h1>

<p>Edges as defined above need no further processing.</p>

<p>Later, we will tie edges to ports to components.</p>

<p>Drawio produces <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">edge</code> facts as <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">mxCell</code> nodes of the graph.  We donâ€™t need to do much more at this point.</p>

